# AltoAI MVP

## Frontend Setup and Running

1. Navigate to the frontend directory:
```bash
cd frontend
```

2. Install dependencies:
```bash
npm install
```

3. Start the development server:
```bash
npm run dev
```

The frontend will be available at http://localhost:5173

Note: Make sure the backend server is running on port 8080 for the frontend to work properly.

## Backend Setup and Running

1. Make sure you have Go installed (version 1.20 or higher)

2. Install dependencies:
```bash
go mod tidy
```

3. Set up environment variables:
- Copy `.env.example` to `.env`
- Fill in your Google OAuth credentials and other required variables

4. Start the backend server:
```bash
go run cmd/main.go
```

The backend will be available at http://localhost:8080

Make sure PostgreSQL is running and configured according to your .env file before starting the backend.


# Build and run
docker-compose up --build

# Or run in background
docker-compose up -d --build

# View logs
docker-compose logs -f

# Stop
docker-compose down

# Restart
docker-compose restart

# Rebuild and restart
docker-compose up --build -d